Excellent place to grab a bite before heading out to Dolores park for a picnic. We got a lemon cream tarte, the idiazabal & membrillo sandwich, and the spicy turkey sandwich. The lemon cream tarte was absolutely to die for, definitely one of the best lemon pastries I've ever had. It's a bit on the pricey side but it's worth the splurge. The spicy turkey sandwich was also incredibly good and the pesto was full of flavor. Note that the sandwiches here are huge so unless you're really hungry you may want to split a sandwich between two people. My only letdown was the idiazabal & membrillo. The first couple bites were good, but after that the jam started tasting too sweet and completely overpowered the cheese. Definitely not worth it for $15. I'll definitely be back when I was to visit Dolores park.

    Things I like
    The passion fruit bavarian cake thing is ok...

    Sandwiches are good although I do prefer deli style subs more.

    I don't buy the bread here since I can schlep ten feet to the Manufactory location from the BFs in my jammies. I'm spoiled :)

    Prices here may seem expensive compared to Safeway, but it's dirt cheap compared to the average $150-200 i spend for 2 ppl at a semi nice restaurant these days.

    Don't be afraid of the wait! I don't know what ppl are talking about the 1 hour wait. I literally come here EVERY Sunday between 12pm to 2pm and my bf and I never had to wait more than 15 min from a line starting outside the store to the cash register. We are also always able to find somewhere to sit despite how crowded it can look in there.

    9/2/2018

    Hands down, one of the best bakeries the Bay Area has to offer! The bread here is sooooooo good, it's always super fresh and just tastes exquisite. Their country loaf is my favorite, crunchy/toasty on the outside and so dense and fluffy on the inside. As far as their baked goods, the banana cream pie is just wow....flaky pie dough, fresh banana, a nice caramel layer inside, and all topped with thick and fresh whipped cream and shavings of chocolate. I've tried to replicate it and haven't even kind of come close!  And any version of a croissant or pain au [fill in the blank] that they make is worth trying!! They make them really light, buttery, and flaky.

    This place is definitely worth sticking through the long lines because the quality of the food they sell is hard to find elsewhere.  If you find yourself losing patience, just know that you will be happy you stuck through it at the end when you're eating the yumminess.
